'''''Star Wars Insider'' 81''' is the eighty-first issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'', released in [[March]] [[2005]]. It started shipping to subscribers on [[March 11]], and began shipping to newsstands on [[March 28]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Comlink (department)|Comlink]]"
*"[[Skywalking]]: News from Around the Galaxy"
*"[[Jedi Library (department)|Jedi Library]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|Turning to The Dark Side]] {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*"[[Drawn by the Force]]" &mdash; [[Star Wars: Episode III — Revenge of the Sith (comic series)|At Last We Will Have Revenge]] {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace|Dan Wallace]]}}
*"[[Set Piece|Technical Readout]]" &mdash; A True Jedi Makes A Noble Sacrifice {{C|by [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*"[[Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master]]" &mdash; None for You, Two for Me! {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; When a Collector Makes His "Own" Collectibles {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet|Steve Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Jabba's Collection]]" &mdash; April 2, 2005 Brings The Force of a Lifetime! {{C|by starwars.hasbro.com}}
*"[[Anchorhead Arcade]]" &mdash; Prepare Yourself, Young Jedi... [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith (video game)|The Sith Want Revenge]] {{C|by Brett Rector}}
*"[[Best of Hyperspace]]" &mdash; Episode III: Twilight of the Jedi {{C|by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Bonnie Burton]]}}
*"[[Laugh It Up, Fuzzball]]"
*[[Bantha Tracks (department)|''Bantha Tracks'']] Vol. 12

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Brett Rector]]}}
*:<small>In late January, a host of principal actors arrived in London for a day of pickup shots as John Williams prepared to work his magic in the famed Abbey Road recording studio to complete the film's musical score.</small>
*"[[The Droids of Episode III: It's a Junkyard Smackdown!]]", {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>Come on inside the galactic junkyard for an early look at some of the menacing (and not so menacing) machines that will appear in ''Revenge of the Sith''.</small>
*"[[I, Jedi (article)|I, Jedi]]" {{C|by Brett Rector}}
*:<small>Obi-Wan Kenobi is one of the most iconic figures in the entire ''Star Wars'' universe, and Ewan McGregor knows it. ''Insider'' spoke to the prolific young actor and found out there's more to this Jedi than simple tricks and nonsense.</small>
*"[[Material World]]" {{C|by Brett Rector}}
*:<small>''Insider'' took a trip into the material empire of ''Revenge of the Sith''{{'s}} costume designer, Trisha Biggar. As we explored the varying textures of Padmé's gowns and Palpatine's robes, we found Darth Vader lurking in the shadows.</small>
*"[[Omega Squad: Targets]]", {{C|by [[Karen Traviss]]}}
*:<small>A group of terrorists has taken a senator hostage in Galactic City on Coruscant, and it's up to Omega Squad to diffuse the dangerous situation.</small>

